{{Quote|It's outrageous that after four trials in the Supreme Court, Nute Gunray is still the Viceroy of the Trade Federation.|[[Sio Bibble]]|<ref name="AotC">{{Film|II}}</ref>}}
The '''Viceroy of the Trade Federation''' was the senior executive position of the [[Trade Federation]] conglomerate. The [[Sith Lord]] [[Darth Sidious]] manipulated [[Nute Gunray]]'s rise to the position, that would allow the [[megacorporation]]'s [[Invasion of Naboo|invasion]] of the [[planet]] [[Naboo]]<ref name="Episode I" /> in [[32 BBY|the following year]],<ref name="Galactic Atlas">''[[Star Wars: Galactic Atlas]]''</ref>  Gunray served as [[Viceroy]] of the Trade Federation during the invasion<ref name="On the Front Lines">''[[Star Wars: On the Front Lines]]''</ref> and, despite facing several trials in the [[Supreme Court]],<ref name="AotC" /> kept the title during the subsequent [[Clone Wars]]. The Viceroy was [[Death|killed]] on [[Mustafar]]<ref name="Episode III">{{Film|III}}</ref> in [[19 BBY]] by Sidious' new [[Sith apprentice|apprentice]], [[Anakin Skywalker|Darth Vader]].<ref name="Galactic Atlas" />

{{Stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
The Viceroy of the Trade Federation title first appeared through Nute Gunray in the [[1999]] film [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''Star Wars'': Episode I ''The Phantom Menace'']], the first installment of the ''[[Star Wars]]'' [[prequel trilogy]].<ref name="Episode I" />

